## AtlasIT Infrastructure & AI Addendum

This addendum provides required context on the infrastructure and AI architecture powering AtlasIT. It supplements the Researcher prompt and design documents.

---

### ☁️ Deployment Architecture (Cloudflare-First)

AtlasIT is deployed primarily via **Cloudflare Workers**, with supporting use of **Google Cloud Functions** where necessary. It is fully serverless and edge-distributed.

#### Core Components

| Component          | Technology                                      |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------- |
| MCP Orchestrator   | Cloudflare Worker (with D1 + KV bindings)       |
| MCP Modules        | Cloudflare Workers or GCP Functions             |
| Deployment Tooling | Wrangler (Cloudflare CLI)                       |
| State Storage      | Cloudflare KV (ephemeral), D1 (structured)      |
| Secrets            | Cloudflare Secrets / GCP Secret Manager         |
| Messaging          | GCP Pub/Sub OR service-dispatch (Cloudflare)    |
| Scheduling         | Worker-level CRON + MCP-managed scheduled tasks |

#### Cloudflare Features Used

* **Dispatch namespaces** for inter-worker RPC
* **Environment bindings** for secrets and tokens
* **KV namespaces** for agent-level state and TTL-based tracking
* **Durable Object compatibility** (planned)

---

### 🤖 Embedded AI Agents

AtlasIT includes real-time and scheduled AI-based automations.

#### Current Agent Types

| AI Agent Type              | Purpose                                             |
| -------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| Docs Generator             | Summarizes FlowEvents into Markdown/Confluence logs |
| Cost Report Analyzer       | Parses BQ/Firestore data for spend patterns         |
| Slack Approval Interpreter | Parses Slack interactive message responses          |
| GitHub AI Assistant        | Rewrites MCP module stubs, CI files, etc.           |

#### AI Invocation

* MCP triggers AI agents via internal API (dispatch or direct `fetch()`)
* All AI events generate `FlowEvent` + `AuditLog`
* Tokens are managed in Cloudflare Secrets only

#### AI Models in Use

* GPT-4 / GPT-4o via OpenAI API
* Claude 3 (internal only)
* Occasional use of Together.ai or Mistral (local, when applicable)

---

### 🛡️ Security & Observability

* All secrets and tokens injected via Wrangler CLI (`wrangler secret put`)
* AI agent interactions are fully logged and auditable
* MCP worker enforces retry, validation, fallback for every agent call
* Slack + email alerts are routed via MCP Event Bus

---

### ✅ Researcher Instructions

Use this infrastructure context to:

* Propose module deployment strategies with **Cloudflare Workers as the default target**
* Leverage AI for summarization, detection, and auto-remediation logic where appropriate
* Ensure **cost models** reflect serverless event-scale billing (e.g., OpenAI token cost, Cloudflare CPU cycles, Pub/Sub pricing)
* Align all agent/module behaviors with **MCP standards** (observable, stateless, forkable, recoverable)

Reference this addendum when defining workflows, module structure, or cost implications.
